Percent of People with Disabilities, Living in an Institution

Summary

Percent of People with Disabilities, Living in an Institution
According to the U.S. Census, institutional living includes correctional facilities, nursing homes and mental hospitals. The lowest state or territory was Arizona (AZ) at 35.4%. The highest state or territory was Rhode Island (RI) at 79.6%. Detailed information is available below in the map and table below.
Source: 2015-2019 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates.
